#!   DESCRIPTION="&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;This Custom Transformer enables to read a CKAN or a CSW server and extract the requested metadata records.  Once the metadata records are extracted, they are transformed from their hierarchcal structure (JSON for CKAN and XML for CSW) into a flattened FME attribute and list features.  The parameters allow great flexibility on how the CKAN or CSW server are requested.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;Note: No modification other then the JSON/XML flattening is performed on the metadata records read from the CKAN/CSW server.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Input: One feature to signal the start of the metadata server extraction.    &lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Résultats: The features resulting from the CKAN or the CSW server extraction.  One output feature for each metadata record read.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Métadonnées invalides: Used to output ID not found in the CKAN or CSW server. On ly used when the parameter &lt;em&gt;IDENTIFIANT&lt;/em&gt; is used.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;UUID_invalide: Used when the ID is not a valid UUID. On ly used when the parameter &lt;em&gt;IDENTIFIANT&lt;/em&gt; is used.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;SOURCE_URL: The source URL (web address) of the target CKAN or CSW server. There are 6 pre-defined source url and one user defined address (drop down bix):&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;FGP-STAGING_INTERNE: Address of the external internal FGP staging server;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;FGP-STAGING-EXTERNE:Address of the internal internal FGP staging server;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;FGP-PROD_INTERNE: Address of the internal FGP production server ;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;FGP-PROD-EXTERNE: Address of the externall FGP production server;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;OPENDATA-STAGING: Address of the Open Data staging server;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;OPENDATA-PROD: Address of the Open Data production server;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;PYCSW-INTERNAL: Address of the internal PYCSW server;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;CUSTOM-CSW/CKAN: Custom URL address of a CKAN or CSW server to be supplied by the user in the &lt;em&gt;CUSTOM_URL&lt;/em&gt; parameter.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_URL: The address of the server to be used when &lt;em&gt;CUSTOM-CSW/CKAN&lt;/em&gt; option is choosen with &lt;em&gt;SOURCE_URL&lt;/em&gt; parameter. &lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;CKAN_FILER: String to be used with CKAN server to filter the result. Ex.: fq=collection:fgp where &lt;em&gt;fq&lt;/em&gt; is the CKAN reserved word for filtering, &lt;em&gt;collection&lt;/em&gt; is a the name of a key in the JSON document and &lt;em&gt;fgp&lt;/em&gt; is the requested value for the filtering;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_CSW_SCHEMA: Drop down box specifying the output schema to use to generate the metadata records (default: http://www.iso tc211.org/2005/ gmd). Used with CSW server.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_CSW_VERSION: Drop down box specifying the version of the CSW server to use (default: 2.0.2)&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_URL_CSW_TYPENAMES: Dropdown box specifying which entities must be queried from the information model (default: gmd:MD_Met adata). Used with CSW server.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_CSW_LIST_NAME: Dropdown box specifying the name of the FME list attribute used to explode the list attribute . (fefault MD_Metadata{}) Used with CSW server.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;IDENTIFIANT:  UUID identifying the ID of the metadata record to extract from the server. Used with CSW and CKAN server.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_URL_BY_ID_ATT_NAME:&lt;em&gt; Not used any more&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;CSW_ANY_TEXT_FILTER: A string to be used to filter the metadata records.  Any string canbe used.  can filter any field of the metadata record.  Used with CSW server. &lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note&lt;/strong&gt;:  For more information on the use of the parameters of the CSW server, refer to the official OGC documentation &lt;a href=&quot;https://portal.opengeospatial.org/files/?artifact_id=77949&quot;&gt; OGC PDF documentation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;"
