#!   MARKDOWN_DESCRIPTION="**Description**&#10;&#10;This Custom Transformer enables to read a CKAN or a CSW server and extract the requested metadata records.  Once the metadata records are extracted, they are transformed from their hierarchcal structure (JSON for CKAN and XML for CSW) into a flattened FME attribute and list features.  The parameters allow great flexibility on how the CKAN or CSW server are requested.&#10;&#10;Note: No modification other then the JSON/XML flattening is performed on the metadata records read from the CKAN/CSW server.&#10;&#10;**Input Ports**&#10;&#10;  - Input: One feature to signal the start of the metadata server extraction.    &#10;&#10;**Output Ports**&#10;&#10;  - Résultats: The features resulting from the CKAN or the CSW server extraction.  One output feature for each metadata record read.&#10;  - Métadonnées invalides: Used to output ID not found in the CKAN or CSW server. On ly used when the parameter _IDENTIFIANT_ is used.&#10;  - UUID_invalide: Used when the ID is not a valid UUID. On ly used when the parameter _IDENTIFIANT_ is used.&#10;&#10;**Parameters**&#10; &#10;  - SOURCE_URL: The source URL (web address) of the target CKAN or CSW server. There are 6 pre-defined source url and one user defined address (drop down bix):&#10;    - FGP-STAGING_INTERNE: Address of the external internal FGP staging server;&#10;    -  FGP-STAGING-EXTERNE:Address of the internal internal FGP staging server;&#10;    -  FGP-PROD_INTERNE: Address of the internal FGP production server ;&#10;    -  FGP-PROD-EXTERNE: Address of the externall FGP production server;&#10;    - OPENDATA-STAGING: Address of the Open Data staging server;&#10;    - OPENDATA-PROD: Address of the Open Data production server;&#10;    - PYCSW-INTERNAL: Address of the internal PYCSW server;&#10;    - CUSTOM-CSW/CKAN: Custom URL address of a CKAN or CSW server to be supplied by the user in the _CUSTOM_URL_ parameter.&#10;  - CUSTOM_URL: The address of the server to be used when _CUSTOM-CSW/CKAN_ option is choosen with _SOURCE_URL_ parameter. &#10;  - CKAN_FILER: String to be used with CKAN server to filter the result. Ex.: fq=collection:fgp where _fq_ is the CKAN reserved word for filtering, _collection_ is a the name of a key in the JSON document and _fgp_ is the requested value for the filtering;&#10;  - CUSTOM_CSW_SCHEMA: Drop down box specifying the output schema to use to generate the metadata records (default: http://www.iso tc211.org/2005/ gmd). Used with CSW server.&#10;  - CUSTOM_CSW_VERSION: Drop down box specifying the version of the CSW server to use (default: 2.0.2)&#10;  - CUSTOM_URL_CSW_TYPENAMES: Dropdown box specifying which entities must be queried from the information model (default: gmd:MD_Met adata). Used with CSW server.&#10;  - CUSTOM_CSW_LIST_NAME: Dropdown box specifying the name of the FME list attribute used to explode the list attribute . (fefault MD_Metadata{}) Used with CSW server.&#10;  - IDENTIFIANT:  UUID identifying the ID of the metadata record to extract from the server. Used with CSW and CKAN server.&#10; - CUSTOM_URL_BY_ID_ATT_NAME:_ Not used any more_.&#10; - CSW_ANY_TEXT_FILTER: A string to be used to filter the metadata records.  Any string canbe used.  can filter any field of the metadata record.  Used with CSW server. &#10;&#10;**Note**:  For more information on the use of the parameters of the CSW server, refer to the official OGC documentation [ OGC PDF documentation](https://portal.opengeospatial.org/files/?artifact_id=77949).&#10;    "
